# Apple Brie Bacon Panini with Preserves

> Makes 2 sandwiches. #emma

- Bread | Sourdough or ciabatta, 4 slices | 
- Apple | 1 | 
- Brie Cheese | 8 slices | 
- Bacon | Cooked, 4 slices | 
- Butter | 2 tbsp | 
- Fruit Preserves | Fig, 2 tbsp | 

Preheat your panini press.

Arrange the sandwiches: spread fruit preserves on one slice of bread, then layer 2 slices of Brie, 2 slices of bacon, apple slices, and another 2 slices of Brie. Top with a second slice of bread. Repeat for the second sandwich.

Butter the outsides of the sandwiches.

Cook the sandwiches in the preheated panini press until the bread is toasted and the cheese is melted, about 3-5 minutes.

Enjoy your Apple Brie Bacon Panini with preserves!
